cs.DS, cs.GT, cs.DM, cs.CG, cs.AL. 

The paper deals with a data structure for computing revenue in a shortest path tree game, which involves graph theory and optimization. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AL (Computational Geometry) are likely categories. The use of game theory and revenue computation suggests cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper also involves the analysis of graphs and their properties, which could fall under cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
